",["$r","h3",null,{"id":"support-for-metadata-tags","children":"Support for Document Metadata "}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":["In HTML, document metadata tags like ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<title>"}],", ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<link>"}],", and ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<meta>"}]," are reserved for placement in the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<head>"}]," section of the document. In React, the component that decides what metadata is appropriate for the app may be very far from the place where you render the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<head>"}]," or React does not render the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<head>"}]," at all. In the past, these elements would need to be inserted manually in an effect, or by libraries like ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/nfl/react-helmet","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":["$r","code",null,{"children":"react-helmet"}]}],", and required careful handling when server rendering a React application."]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":"In React 19, we’re adding support for rendering document metadata tags in components natively:"}],"
",["$r","pre",null,{"children":["$r","code",null,{"className":"language-js","meta":"{5-8}","children":"function BlogPost({post}) {
  return (
    <article>
      <h1>{post.title}</h1>
      <title>{post.title}</title>
      <meta name="author" content="Josh" />
      <link rel="author" href="https://twitter.com/joshcstory/" />
      <meta name="keywords" content={post.keywords} />
      <p>
        Eee equals em-see-squared...
      </p>
    </article>
  );
}
"}]}],"
",["$r","p",null,{"children":["When React renders this component, it will see the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<title>"}]," ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<link>"}]," and ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<meta>"}]," tags, and automatically hoist them to the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"<head>"}]," section of document. By supporting these metadata tags natively, we’re able to ensure they work with client-only apps, streaming SSR, and Server Components."]}],"
",["$r","Note",null,{"children":[["$r","h4",null,{"id":"you-may-still-want-a-metadata-library","children":"You may still want a Metadata library "}],["$r","p",null,{"children":["For simple use cases, rendering Document Metadata as tags may be suitable, but libraries can offer more powerful features like overriding generic metadata with specific metadata based on the current route. These features make it easier for frameworks and libraries like ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/nfl/react-helmet","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":["$r","code",null,{"children":"react-helmet"}]}]," to support metadata tags, rather than replace them."]}]]}],"
